India Sets 26% Rate Cap for Loans to Microfinance Companies

-- B y   K a r t i k   G o y a l
-- 
2011-05-03T05:42:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/india-sets-26-rate-cap-for-loans-to-microfinance-companies.html
India 's central bank said banks should
cap loans to microfinance companies at 26 percent for the funds
to be eligible for the so-called priority sector lending.  Banks have also been asked to ensure they cap margins to 12
percent, the  Reserve Bank  of India said in its annual policy
review. The central bank also said for the loans to be eligible
as priority sector the total indebtedness of the borrower should
not exceed 50,000 rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kartik Goyal in Mumbai at 
 kgoyal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephanie Phang at   sphang@bloomberg.net  